<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-201] When using o2iblnd, peer_timeout should be at least twice the value of the ko2iblnd keepalive option</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-201</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Question from Nic Henke (he comment originally came from Bugzilla ticket&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://projectlava.xyratex.com/show_bug.cgi?id=24404&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://projectlava.xyratex.com/show_bug.cgi?id=24404&lt;/a&gt;). Doug Oucharek is following up with Nic.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When using o2iblnd, peer_timeout should be at least twice the value of the ko2iblnd keepalive option.&lt;br/&gt;
--&amp;gt;&amp;gt; (Cray question) Shouldn&apos;t both be expanded by 5/4 to handle the timeout granularity that most LNDs use?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-50&quot; title=&quot;The Lustre Ops Manual should doc LNET/LND options for peer_timeout and avoid_asym_router_failure&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUDOC-50&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUDOC-50&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for context.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
